b'Mr. President, the people who sent us here still have big dreams and big hopes. Let\xe2\x80\x99s help those dreams grow and their hopes flourish.'
b'There is NO doubt of that.'
b'Despite challenges, despite big-govt\xe2\x80\x99s creep into our lives, despite armed EPA agents, we continue to live in greatest country in the world.'
b'I believe our government should be helping, not hindering, these efforts.'
b'And I think most of us can agree that we must unleash the country\xe2\x80\x99s enormous economic potential once again.'
b'We want a government that holds dear what our fathers knew \xe2\x80\x93 that all powers are derived from the consent of the governed.'
b'We want to continue to live in the best country in the world, a country of unlimited opportunity, a country of Alaska-sized dreams.'
b'We want our children to be safe and secure and we want the same for our neighbor.'
b'We want to be strong here at home which will help us be respected once again by our allies and feared by our adversaries.'
b'We all want the very best for the people we represent and the states we speak for.'
b'let me close with a few words about how I view my mission here.\nI suspect it doesn\xe2\x80\x99t differ from what most of us here hope to accomplish.'
b'And finally we must challenge the conventional wisdom that the federal government\xe2\x80\x99s power &  intrusiveness should always be expanding'
b'Fourth: while I believe in a limited fed. govt, we must recognize where the fed. govt DOES have responsibilities -- like protecting our Vets'
b'Third: we must get back to the rule of law.'
b'Second, we need more, not less, access to our federal lands. As Americans, these are OUR lands \xe2\x80\x93 not the @Interior or @BLMNational'
b'Let me suggest a few ideas: First \xe2\x80\x93 We MUST stop delaying economic projects that benefit our citizens.'
b'We must work to once again unleash the great potential that is Alaska and America & we must work to reinvigorate faith in the American dream'
b'Congress has a job to do. We must work to address the anxiety and frustration of the people we serve.'
b'What the American people are telling us, is that they want a federal government that helps ignite their hope, not smother it.'
b'Our citizens are telling us that their government has gone well beyond deriving its powers from the consent of the governed.'
b'And judging from what Americans are telling us, the reach of the federal government has exceeded its limits.'
b'Since the founding of this country, we\xe2\x80\x99ve had important debates right here on this floor about the role of the fed. government in our lives.'
b'Yes, we have major challenges like all states. But in Alaska, we still have hope, we still dream big dreams. TAPS helps fuel these dreams.'
b'I\xe2\x80\x99m standing in support of what has defined this country for centuries: The idea of the American dream.'
b'In supporting Keystone, I\xe2\x80\x99m  standing for a larger principle. The ideal that the fed. govt should be a partner in progress. Not an obstacle.'
b'Today I stand in support of Keystone. As an Alaskan I feel it\xe2\x80\x99s important to talk about this bill & the importance of energy infrastructure'
